                    <h3 class="p-work-overview--occ p-work-overview__title" id="information-architecture">
                      Information Architecture</h3>
                    <div class="p-work-overview__description">In the OCC project, the Information Architecture
                      (IA) was an important aspect of the UX design process. Our team
                      conducted a thorough analysis of the existing IA and determined the key elements that needed
                      to be included in the new
                      design. The main goal of our IA work was to create a clear and intuitive structure that
                      would enable users to easily
                      navigate and find the information they needed.
                      To achieve this, we developed a hierarchical organization of the content and functionality,
                      breaking down the site into
                      categories, sections, and sub-pages. This helped us to create a clear and logical path for
                      users to follow as they moved
                      through the site. Additionally, we used clear and concise labeling to help users understand
                      the purpose of each section
                      and what they could expect to find there.
                      The IA work was also informed by our user research and testing, which allowed us to validate
                      our design decisions and
                      ensure that our IA was meeting the needs of our users. As a result, we were able to create a
                      highly effective and
                      intuitive IA that helped users achieve their goals quickly and easily.
                    </div>
